radio_info.short: KYAK 106 is Carriacou’s own homegrown fm radio station, reflecting the spirit, culture, uniqueness and friendly nature of our people. From its broadcasting inception in
radio_info.rest:
1996, KYAK 106 has continuously brought our listeners a variety of West Indian music including reggae, calypso, and soca and high lighting our own talented local musicians. KYAK 106 also brings informational programming as well as offering a voice for our listeners to express their
opinions and comments on a wide variety of concernsMany thanks to our devoted staff. We wish to thank all of our advertisers & sponsors who have made it possible for us to pay our operating expenses. And of course, not forgetting you, our listening audience! Thank you for making KYAK 106 what it is today and inspiring us to continue bringing you… the beat of the grenadines.

Your truly,
Kim Mills
Michael Ward

Bringing together Carriacou, Petite Martinique and Grenada’s communities as well as sharing our culture with our neighboring islands has always been our main aim and the strong support of our listening audience has given credence to the success of our mission.

It’s not an easy road KYAK106 has traveled since 1996 but we have grown in many ways. We have been on the air for 14 years now are proud of our accomplishments and pledge our continued dedication to our listeners for at least another 10 years! We are very pleased to be able to reach more of you further away from home, with the advent of streaming online.

radio_info.short: Grenada is an island country and sovereign state consisting of the island of Grenada and six smaller islands at the southern end of the Grenadines
radio_info.rest:
in the southeastern Caribbean Sea. Grenada is located northwest of Trinidad and Tobago, northeast of Venezuela, and southwest of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines.

Its size is 344 square kilometres (133 sq mi), with an estimated population of 110,000. Its capital is St. George's. The national bird of Grenada is the critically endangered Grenada Dove.

radio_info.short: Welcome to the Harbour Light! from Carriacou, Grenada Christian Radio AM1400, 94.5, 92.3FM & Internet streaming Quick Player The Harbour Light of the Windwards is
radio_info.rest:
Light of the Windwards is a distinctively Christian radio station and located on the beautiful 13 square-mile island of Carriacou, a dependency of Grenada in the Windward islands of the West Indies.  Our purpose is to glorify the Lord Jesus Christ as God, the Creator; to lift Him up as the only way to be saved from your sin and God's impending judgment; and to provide educational and public service programmes.  The Harbour Light of the Windwards is a non-profit, non-commercial, Christian radio facility. We invite you to listen to our online broadcast stream.  The purpose of this website is to acquaint you with what we are doing, how we are doing it and who's doing it.  Our prayer is that you will find that your visit with us has been helpful and a blessing.

The Harbour Light of the Windwards...

Clearly presents the Gospel, the narrow charted course to God's Heaven.

Makes available the only accurate map for a victorious voyage through the Christian life (the Bible).

Exposes the devil's dangerous submerged rocks and reefs that would shipwreck the soul.

Signals detailed instructions on how to successfully navigate in any storm of life.

Operates from an immovable position on the Word of God.
 


 
I send thee to open their eyes,
and to turn them from darkness to light,
and from the power of Satan unto God,
that they may receive forgiveness of sins,
and inheritance among them which are
sanctified by faith that is in me.  Acts 26:18
